				<p><p>A quadrature encoder has two output channels.</p>

<p><b>Pulses per revolution</b><br>
Looking at <em>one</em> output channel of the encoder, the number of pulses per revolution is the number of rising edges per revolution.</p>

<p><b>Counts per revolution</b><br>
Combining the two encoder outputs, and counting every rising and falling edge gives the number of counts per resolution.</p>

<p>CPR = 4 x PPR</p>

<p><img src="https://i.stack.imgur.com/70jj8.jpg" alt="Quadrature Encoder Signal"></p>

<p>As for Transitions and State Changes per revolution, I would guess that these are equivalent to Counts.</p>
